WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.350 --> 00:00:04.887
NULL:  Every trust, every habit, every careless click -

2
00:00:04.887 --> 00:00:06.588
I will exploit it.

3
00:00:06.888 --> 00:00:09.035
VEGA:  Not tonight. And the easiest door of all

4
00:00:09.035 --> 00:00:10.968
is a person who hasn't been trained.

5
00:00:11.268 --> 00:00:13.450
NOVA:  So the people are the perimeter too?

6
00:00:13.750 --> 00:00:16.230
VEGA:  The most-attacked one. Let's defend them.

7
00:00:17.280 --> 00:00:21.209
NULL:  Walls and towers? Tedious. People are so much

8
00:00:21.209 --> 00:00:22.518
easier to fool.

9
00:00:22.818 --> 00:00:25.346
VEGA:  And that is why the strongest controls guard

10
00:00:25.346 --> 00:00:26.898
the people, and their data.

11
00:00:27.948 --> 00:00:30.495
VEGA:  Layer three is human. Train them, trust them

12
00:00:30.495 --> 00:00:32.348
carefully, and honor their data.

13
00:00:32.648 --> 00:00:36.266
Three families keep the pact: Awareness & Training,

14
00:00:36.266 --> 00:00:38.536
Personnel Security, and Privacy.

15
00:00:39.586 --> 00:00:42.637
NOVA:  AT, PS, PT - these sound very human.

16
00:00:42.637 --> 00:00:44.248
Who are we meeting?

17
00:00:45.298 --> 00:00:47.898
VEGA:  The Drillmaster, Awareness and Training.

18
00:00:48.198 --> 00:00:50.664
VEGA:  A trained citizen spots the trick at the

19
00:00:50.664 --> 00:00:51.958
gate before it opens.

20
00:00:52.258 --> 00:00:55.268
VEGA:  In reality, that's security and privacy training so

21
00:00:55.268 --> 00:00:58.218
people recognize and resist threats like phishing.

22
00:00:59.268 --> 00:01:01.730
NOVA:  What is 'phishing,' exactly?

23
00:01:02.030 --> 00:01:04.681
VEGA:  Bait for people. A message that looks legitimate

24
00:01:04.681 --> 00:01:06.228
but is a trap - and it's how

25
00:01:06.228 --> 00:01:07.830
most breaches actually begin.

26
00:01:08.880 --> 00:01:11.222
NOVA:  How do you stop a perfect phishing email?

27
00:01:11.522 --> 00:01:14.512
VEGA:  You train the human. AT-2 builds the reflex

28
00:01:14.512 --> 00:01:16.599
to hang up on the kind of call

29
00:01:16.599 --> 00:01:17.642
we opened with.

30
00:01:18.692 --> 00:01:21.692
VEGA:  And AT-3 trains people for their particular role.

31
00:01:25.192 --> 00:01:29.036
ARCHIVIST:  Provide security and privacy literacy training to system

32
00:01:29.036 --> 00:01:33.565
users (including managers, senior executives, and contractors): As

33
00:01:33.565 --> 00:01:36.448
part of initial training for new users and

34
00:01:36.448 --> 00:01:39.468
[organization-defined frequency] thereafter;

35
00:01:40.518 --> 00:01:43.100
VEGA:  The cheapest firewall you own is an alert

36
00:01:43.100 --> 00:01:43.478
human.

37
00:01:49.118 --> 00:01:52.144
VEGA:  The Drillmaster's oath. The sharpest blade is an

38
00:01:52.144 --> 00:01:52.838
alert mind.

39
00:01:53.888 --> 00:01:56.448
VEGA:  The Oathkeeper, Personnel Security.

40
00:01:56.748 --> 00:01:59.826
NULL:  Every guard you hire... could be mine.

41
00:02:00.126 --> 00:02:03.512
VEGA:  In reality, that's screening people, adjusting access when

42
00:02:03.512 --> 00:02:06.314
they move or leave, and guarding against insider

43
00:02:06.314 --> 00:02:06.606
risk.

44
00:02:07.656 --> 00:02:10.936
VEGA:  PS-3 screens people before they're trusted with access.

45
00:02:14.156 --> 00:02:16.138
NOVA:  And when a guard leaves?

46
00:02:16.438 --> 00:02:18.961
VEGA:  PS-4 reclaims the keys, on the way out

47
00:02:18.961 --> 00:02:19.558
the door.

48
00:02:20.656 --> 00:02:24.930
ARCHIVIST:  Upon termination of individual employment: Disable system access

49
00:02:24.930 --> 00:02:26.332
within [time period];

50
00:02:27.382 --> 00:02:29.843
VEGA:  Access should follow the person, and leave when

51
00:02:29.843 --> 00:02:30.262
they do.

52
00:02:37.682 --> 00:02:40.193
VEGA:  The Oathkeeper's oath. Trust is earned at the

53
00:02:40.193 --> 00:02:41.922
gate, and returned at the door.

54
00:02:42.972 --> 00:02:46.830
VEGA:  The Privacy Herald, P-T, Processing and Transparency of

55
00:02:46.830 --> 00:02:47.812
personal data.

56
00:02:48.112 --> 00:02:51.129
NOVA:  Privacy gets its own family now? That must

57
00:02:51.129 --> 00:02:52.134
be pretty new?

58
00:02:52.434 --> 00:02:56.334
VEGA:  In reality, that's processing people's personal data lawfully

59
00:02:56.334 --> 00:02:59.019
and openly - with notice and consent where

60
00:02:59.019 --> 00:02:59.594
required.

61
00:03:00.644 --> 00:03:03.746
NOVA:  P-I-I keeps coming up.

62
00:03:04.046 --> 00:03:07.645
VEGA:  Personally identifiable information - the data that points

63
00:03:07.645 --> 00:03:10.065
to a real human being. Privacy is about

64
00:03:10.065 --> 00:03:11.926
protecting it, and the person.

65
00:03:12.976 --> 00:03:17.156
VEGA:  PT-2 demands a documented authority to process personal

66
00:03:17.156 --> 00:03:17.536
data.

67
00:03:19.476 --> 00:03:22.533
VEGA:  And PT-5 gives people honest notice of how

68
00:03:22.533 --> 00:03:23.916
their data is used.

69
00:03:25.976 --> 00:03:29.462
VEGA:  Authority first, then purpose and notice, then consent

70
00:03:29.462 --> 00:03:32.496
where required, and process only as authorized.

71
00:03:32.796 --> 00:03:35.960
NOVA:  So - get permission when it's needed, and

72
00:03:35.960 --> 00:03:38.738
be honest about how the data's used?

73
00:03:39.788 --> 00:03:43.610
ARCHIVIST:  Determine and document the [authority] that permits the

74
00:03:43.610 --> 00:03:47.224
[processing] of personally identifiable information;

75
00:03:48.274 --> 00:03:51.914
VEGA:  Security protects the data. Privacy honors the person.

76
00:03:58.574 --> 00:04:01.535
VEGA:  The Privacy Herald's oath. By what right, for

77
00:04:01.535 --> 00:04:03.574
what purpose, with whose leave?

78
00:04:04.624 --> 00:04:07.335
VEGA:  Not every control is a firewall. Some are

79
00:04:07.335 --> 00:04:09.384
a habit, a contract, a promise.

80
00:04:13.224 --> 00:04:17.190
NOVA:  Scenario: a leaver kept their access. Which guardian

81
00:04:17.190 --> 00:04:18.486
dropped the ball?

82
00:04:18.786 --> 00:04:22.502
A departing administrator still has their access a

83
00:04:22.502 --> 00:04:24.954
week later. Which control failed?

84
00:04:25.254 --> 00:04:30.754
Your options. A. PS-4 Personnel Termination. B. AT-2

85
00:04:30.754 --> 00:04:35.302
Awareness Training. C. PT-5 Privacy Notice.

86
00:04:35.602 --> 00:04:38.504
NOVA:  Pause here and lock in your answer.

87
00:04:45.554 --> 00:04:49.431
VEGA:  The answer is A. PS-4 Personnel Termination. PS-4,

88
00:04:49.431 --> 00:04:54.394
Personnel Termination, revokes access the moment someone leaves.

89
00:04:55.444 --> 00:04:57.820
VEGA:  And which guardian is the newcomer to the

90
00:04:57.820 --> 00:04:58.284
catalog?

91
00:04:58.584 --> 00:05:01.295
Which family is new in Revision 5 and

92
00:05:01.295 --> 00:05:03.712
governs personal-data processing?

93
00:05:04.012 --> 00:05:07.843
Your options. A. AT - Training. B. PS

94
00:05:07.843 --> 00:05:11.674
- Personnel. C. PT - PII Processing &

95
00:05:11.674 --> 00:05:13.020
Transparency.

96
00:05:13.320 --> 00:05:16.222
NOVA:  Pause here and lock in your answer.

97
00:05:23.272 --> 00:05:26.310
VEGA:  The answer is C. PT - PII Processing

98
00:05:26.310 --> 00:05:30.950
& Transparency. PT, PII Processing and Transparency, is

99
00:05:30.950 --> 00:05:34.072
the privacy family new in Revision 5.

100
00:05:35.122 --> 00:05:38.294
NOVA:  Notebook: the strongest controls aren't always technical -

101
00:05:38.294 --> 00:05:40.864
sometimes they're just people keeping promises.

102
00:05:41.164 --> 00:05:43.804
VEGA:  People kept, the pact honored.

103
00:05:44.104 --> 00:05:47.556
NULL:  Then I'll strike where no one is even

104
00:05:47.556 --> 00:05:49.422
looking. Your plans.

105
00:05:49.722 --> 00:05:52.162
VEGA:  Then it's time to meet the High Council.
